\subsection*{Step 3: Speed after 20 seconds}
To calculate the speed after 20 seconds if the acceleration remains constant:
\[v = v_i + at.\]\[v = 0 + 4.97 \times 20 = 99.4 \, \text{m/s.}\]
To convert this speed back to mph:
\[v = 99.4 \times \frac{3600}{1609.34} \approx 177 \, \text{mph.}\]

\subsection*{Final Answers}
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Acceleration:} \(4.97 \, \text{m/s}^2\)
    \item \textbf{Speed after 20 seconds:} \(177 \, \text{mph}\)
\end{itemize}
